{"id":81,"parent_id":80,"book_id":95,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":81,"title":"Mosiah 1","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mosiah","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1","content":[["div",[".title",["span.dominant","The Book of Mosiah"]],[".titleNumber","Chapter 1"],[".studySummary",["i","King Benjamin teaches his sons the language and prophecies of their fathers—Their religion and civilization have been preserved because of the records kept on the various plates—Mosiah is chosen as king and is given custody of the records and other things. About 130–124",["span.small","B.C."]]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.1","order":"05.19.001.8477"},["b","1"],"And now there was no more contention in all the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"land of Zarahemla"],", among all the people who belonged to king Benjamin, so that king Benjamin had continual peace all the remainder of his days."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.2","order":"05.19.001.8478"},["b","2"],"And it came to pass that he had three",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"sons"],"; and he called their names Mosiah, and Helorum, and Helaman. And he caused that they should be",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_2b"},"taught"],"in all the",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_2c"},"language"],"of his fathers, that thereby they might become men of understanding; and that they might know concerning the prophecies which had been spoken by the mouths of their fathers, which were delivered them by the hand of the Lord."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.3","order":"05.19.001.8479"},["b","3"],"And he also taught them concerning the records which were engraven on the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"plates of brass"],", saying: My sons, I would that ye should remember that were it not for these",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_3b"},"plates"],", which contain these records and these commandments, we must have suffered in",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_3c"},"ignorance"],", even at this present time, not knowing the mysteries of God."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.4","order":"05.19.001.8480"},["b","4"],"For it were not possible that our father, Lehi, could have remembered all these things, to have taught them to his children, except it were for the help of these plates; for he having been taught in the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_4a"},"language"],"of the Egyptians therefore he could read these engravings, and teach them to his children, that thereby they could teach them to their children, and so fulfilling the commandments of God, even down to this present time."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.5","order":"05.19.001.8481"},["b","5"],"I say unto you, my sons,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"were"],"it not for these things, which have been kept and",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_5b"},"preserved"],"by the hand of God, that we might",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_5c"},"read"],"and understand of his",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_5d"},"mysteries"],", and have his",["sup","e"],["a",{"href":"fn_5e"},"commandments"],"always before our eyes, that even our fathers would have dwindled in unbelief, and we should have been like unto our brethren, the Lamanites, who know nothing concerning these things, or even do not believe them when they are taught them, because of the",["sup","f"],["a",{"href":"fn_5f"},"traditions"],"of their fathers, which are not correct."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.6","order":"05.19.001.8482"},["b","6"],"O my sons, I would that ye should remember that these sayings are true, and also that these records are",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"true"],". And behold, also the plates of Nephi, which contain the records and the sayings of our fathers from the time they left Jerusalem until now, and they are true; and we can know of their surety because we have them before our eyes."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.7","order":"05.19.001.8483"},["b","7"],"And now, my sons, I would that ye should remember to",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"search"],"them diligently, that ye may profit thereby; and I would that ye should",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_7b"},"keep"],"the commandments of God, that ye may",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_7c"},"prosper"],"in the land according to the",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_7d"},"promises"],"which the Lord made unto our fathers."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.8","order":"05.19.001.8484"},["b","8"],"And many more things did king Benjamin teach his sons, which are not written in this book."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.9","order":"05.19.001.8485"},["b","9"],"And it came to pass that after king Benjamin had made an end of teaching his sons, that he waxed",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_9a"},"old"],", and he saw that he must very soon go the way of all the earth; therefore, he thought it expedient that he should confer the kingdom upon one of his sons."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.10","order":"05.19.001.8486"},["b","10"],"Therefore, he had Mosiah brought before him; and these are the words which he spake unto him, saying: My son, I would that ye should make a proclamation throughout all this land among all this",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"people"],", or the people of Zarahemla, and the people of Mosiah who dwell in the land, that thereby they may be gathered together; for on the morrow I shall proclaim unto this my people out of mine own mouth that thou art a",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_10b"},"king"],"and a ruler over this people, whom the Lord our God hath given us."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.11","order":"05.19.001.8487"},["b","11"],"And moreover, I shall give this people a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"name"],", that thereby they may be distinguished above all the people which the Lord God hath brought out of the land of Jerusalem; and this I do because they have been a",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_11b"},"diligent"],"people in keeping the commandments of the Lord."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.12","order":"05.19.001.8488"},["b","12"],"And I give unto them a name that never shall be blotted out, except it be through",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"transgression"],"."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.13","order":"05.19.001.8489"},["b","13"],"Yea, and moreover I say unto you, that if this highly favored people of the Lord should fall into",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"transgression"],", and become a wicked and an adulterous people, that the Lord will deliver them up, that thereby they become",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_13b"},"weak"],"like unto their brethren; and he will no more",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_13c"},"preserve"],"them by his matchless and marvelous power, as he has hitherto preserved our fathers."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.14","order":"05.19.001.8490"},["b","14"],"For I say unto you, that if he had not extended his arm in the preservation of our fathers they must have fallen into the hands of the Lamanites, and become victims to their hatred."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.15","order":"05.19.001.8491"},["b","15"],"And it came to pass that after king Benjamin had made an end of these sayings to his son, that he gave him",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"charge"],"concerning all the affairs of the kingdom."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.16","order":"05.19.001.8492"},["b","16"],"And moreover, he also gave him charge concerning the records which were engraven on the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_16a"},"plates of brass"],"; and also the plates of Nephi; and also, the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_16b"},"sword"],"of Laban, and the",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_16c"},"ball"],"or director, which led our fathers through the wilderness, which was prepared by the hand of the Lord that thereby they might be led, every one according to the heed and diligence which they gave unto him."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.17","order":"05.19.001.8493"},["b","17"],"Therefore, as they were",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"unfaithful"],"they did not prosper nor progress in their journey, but were",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_17b"},"driven"],"back, and incurred the displeasure of God upon them; and therefore they were smitten with famine and sore",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_17c"},"afflictions"],", to stir them up in",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_17d"},"remembrance"],"of their duty."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.18","order":"05.19.001.8494"},["b","18"],"And now, it came to pass that Mosiah went and did as his father had commanded him, and proclaimed unto all the people who were in the land of Zarahemla that thereby they might gather themselves together, to go up to the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"temple"],"to hear the words which his father should speak unto them."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.1a","order":"05.19.001.8495"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.13"},"Omni 1:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/2.15"},"Alma 2:15"],"."],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.2a","order":"05.19.001.8497"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/1.1"},"1 Ne. 1:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/68.25.25,28"},"D&C 68:25 (25, 28)"],"."],["div",{"id":"2b","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.2b","order":"05.19.001.8499"},["b","2b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.1"},"Enos 1:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.15.14-15"},"Mosiah 4:15 (14–15)"],"."],["div",{"id":"2c","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.2c","order":"05.19.001.8501"},["b","2c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/9.32"},"Morm. 9:32"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.3a","order":"05.19.001.8503"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/5.12"},"2 Ne. 5:12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.16"},"Mosiah 1:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/28.20"},"28:20"],"."],["div",{"id":"3b","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.3b","order":"05.19.001.8505"},["b","3b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/3.19.19-20"},"1 Ne. 3:19 (19–20)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.17"},"Omni 1:17"],"."],["div",{"id":"3c","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.3c","order":"05.19.001.8507"},["b","3c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.8"},"Alma 37:8"],"."],["div",{"id":"4a","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.4a","order":"05.19.001.8509"},["b","4a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/1.2"},"1 Ne. 1:2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/3.19"},"3:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/morm/9.32.32-33"},"Morm. 9:32 (32–33)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.64"},"JS—H 1:64"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.5a","order":"05.19.001.8511"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.9"},"Alma 37:9"],"."],["div",{"id":"5b","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.5b","order":"05.19.001.8513"},["b","5b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/scriptures-preservation-of"},"TG Scriptures, Preservation of"],"."],["div",{"id":"5c","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.5c","order":"05.19.001.8515"},["b","5c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/6.6.6-8"},"Deut. 6:6 (6–8)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/34.21"},"2 Chr. 34:21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/15.24.23-24"},"1 Ne. 15:24 (23–24)"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/scriptures-value-of"},"TG Scriptures, Value of"],"."],["div",{"id":"5d","uri":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.5d","order":"05.19.001.8517"},["b","5d"],["a.scriptureRe